{
  "global": "Find the total uncertainty of the mean estimator μ̂ by combining Type A (statistical) and Type B (instrument scale) uncertainty contributions in quadrature.",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Set up the modified estimator μ̂ under the systematic shift X_B",
      "atomics": [
        "Write the shifted measurements as Yᵢ = Xᵢ + X_B for i = 1,...,N where X_B is the same for all measurements",
        "Express μ̂ = (1/N)∑Yᵢ = X̄ + X_B, identifying X̄ = (1/N)∑Xᵢ as the sample mean of the original measurements"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Compute Var(μ̂) by propagating variance through the sum of independent contributions",
      "atomics": [
        "Note that X̄ and X_B are independent random variables, so Var(μ̂) = Var(X̄) + Var(X_B)",
        "Identify Var(X̄) = σ²/N, estimated by s²/N using the unbiased sample standard deviation s",
        "Compute Var(X_B) for a uniform distribution on [-a/2, a/2]: Var(X_B) = a²/12",
        "Write the total variance: Var(μ̂) = s²/N + a²/12"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Express the combined uncertainty as the square root of the total variance",
      "atomics": [
        "Take the square root: uncertainty of μ̂ = √(s²/N + a²/12)"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Verify dimensional consistency: both s²/N and a²/12 have units of [X]², confirming the formula is correct",
    "Check limiting cases: if a→0, uncertainty reduces to s/√N (pure Type A); if N→∞ and s→0, uncertainty reduces to a/√12 (pure Type B)"
  ],
  "gold_actions": {
    "global": "Derive uncertainty(μ̂) = √(s²/N + a²/12) by computing Var(X̄ + X_B) with X_B ~ Uniform(-a/2, a/2).",
    "subtasks": [
      {
        "subtask": "Express μ̂ = X̄ + X_B where X_B is a common additive shift applied to all N measurements",
        "atomics": [
          "Write Yᵢ = Xᵢ + X_B for each measurement, so μ̂ = (1/N)∑(Xᵢ + X_B) = X̄ + X_B",
          "Identify X̄ = (1/N)∑Xᵢ (sample mean of unshifted values) and X_B as a single shared random variable"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Apply variance addition rule using independence of X̄ and X_B",
        "atomics": [
          "Invoke Var(X̄ + X_B) = Var(X̄) + Var(X_B) by independence",
          "Substitute Var(X̄) = s²/N (Type A contribution estimated by unbiased s)",
          "Compute Var(X_B) = (1/12)(a/2 - (-a/2))² = a²/12 (variance of Uniform[-a/2, a/2])",
          "Sum: Var(μ̂) = s²/N + a²/12"
        ]
      },
      {
        "subtask": "Compute the combined uncertainty as √(Var(μ̂))",
        "atomics": [
          "uncertainty(μ̂) = √(s²/N + a²/12)"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "global_atomics": [
      "Confirm units: [s²/N] = [X²] and [a²/12] = [X²], so √(s²/N + a²/12) has units of [X] as required",
      "Check boundary cases: a=0 gives s/√N (recovers Type A only); large N with small s gives a/√12 (recovers Type B only)"
    ]
  }
}
```

FINAL ANSWER: $\sqrt{\dfrac{s^2}{N} + \dfrac{a^2}{12}}$
